{"questionId":"2966654","questionHtml":"<p>Show that the geometric mean and arithmetic mean are equal when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>let all <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> be labelled as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> (or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math> etc.)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Do not accept use of a specific number for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup></mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>n</mi></mfrac></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><mi>n</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"2966654","referenceCode":"23M.3.AHL.TZ1.2di","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that the geometric mean and arithmetic mean are equal when x1=x2=…=xn.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.6—Simple proof"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}